# Batch commits must update the changelog first

Guild update logs, `/whatsnew`, `/about`, release DMs, and `changelog_channel_id` posts all read from `core/changelog.py` and `BOT_VERSION` in `core/config.py`. **Never commit a batch without updating these in the same commit.**

## Before every batch commit

1. **`core/changelog.py`** — add a bullet to `CURRENT_RELEASE_CHANGES` describing the batch (modules moved, commands added, fixes). Use the `**Batch N** — …` or `**Fix** — …` prefix style already in the file.
2. **`core/config.py`** — bump `BOT_VERSION` when shipping (patch for hotfixes, minor for batches). Update `BOT_CHANGELOG` one-line summary to match.
3. **Version archive** — when bumping `BOT_VERSION`, move the previous release bullets into `CHANGELOG_HISTORY` (newest first) with the **previous** version string. Keep `CURRENT_RELEASE_DATE` accurate.
4. **Same commit** — changelog + version changes belong in the **same commit** as the batch code, not a follow-up.

## What triggers guild update logs

- `BOT_VERSION` change → slash sync marker, release announce, update-log embeds
- `CURRENT_RELEASE_CHANGES` → `/whatsnew` page 1, release announce body, showcase embeds
- Do not rely on `BOT_CHANGELOG` env alone; `core/changelog.py` is the curated source

## Commit message pattern

```
Batch N: <short title>.

<optional body>; changelog + BOT_VERSION bump.
```

## Checklist (do not skip)

- [ ] `CURRENT_RELEASE_CHANGES` has a bullet for this batch
- [ ] `BOT_VERSION` bumped if releasing (Railway must match)
- [ ] Previous version archived to `CHANGELOG_HISTORY` when version bumped
- [ ] Changelog staged in the same commit as the batch diff

## Example bullet

```python
"**Batch 17** — `handlers/foo.py`; `tasks/bar_loops.py`; slim `app.py` further",
```
